# Rust build output.
/target
/core/target

# Tauri v2 generated schemas/context (regenerated by tauri-build).
/gen

# Built sidecar binary tree is a large per-platform release artifact, not source.
/binaries/magi*

# Icons: the full `cargo tauri icon` output is large and platform-spread
# (android/, ios/, Store/Square windows tiles, a 512px icon.png). Ignore the
# whole generated set, but COMMIT the exact five files tauri.conf.json
# references so CI never needs to regenerate them. Regenerate the full set from
# ../web/public/openmagi-app-icon.png with `cargo tauri icon`.
/icons/*
!/icons/README.md
!/icons/32x32.png
!/icons/128x128.png
!/icons/128x128@2x.png
!/icons/icon.icns
!/icons/icon.ico

# Cargo lockfile policy: keep it for the app (reproducible desktop builds).
!Cargo.lock
